{"timestamp": "2026-06-06T23:28:45.307726+00:00", "level": "INFO", "logger": "src.lib.openai_agents.streaming_tools", "message": "General PDF Extraction checking final_output: hasattr=True, value=answer='This paper asks how the molar abundance and stoichiometry of phototransduction and Crumbs-complex/rhabdomere-organizing proteins relate to Drosophila melanogaster eye organization and to crumbs mutant phenotypes. Using wild-type fly eyes and crb mutant alleles as the model system, the authors applied an MS Western/GeLC-MS/MS workflow with an isotopically labeled chimeric protein standard covering 43 proteins to quantify absolute protein amounts and ratios. The principal conclusion is that absolute quantification can produce consistent, biologically interpretable molar ratios for eye protein networks: these ratios relate to molecular organization of the eye, support a shift from relative to absolute proteomic measurements, and show that abnormal rhabdomere shape in crb mutants is not broadly explained by changes in most phototransduction protein abundances, although specific allele-associated changes such as reduced Eys in crb11A22 were observed.' summary='Brief paper-level summary based on the Abstract, Results and Discussion, and Conclusions/ Perspectives sections; no gene ID validation was attempted.' items=[PdfExtractionItem(label='main biological question and model system', entity_type='paper-level claim', normalized_id=None, source_mentions=['quantitative relationship between PT machinery and Crumbs protein complex', 'wild-type fly eye', 'crb mutants'], evidence_record_ids=['evidence-90a17c9c05784b35']), PdfExtractionItem(label='key experimental approach', entity_type='method', normalized_id=None, source_mentions=['MS Western workflow', 'GeLC-MS/MS', 'isotopically labelled QconCAT-like CP standards', '264 kDa CP', '43 unique proteins'], evidence_record_ids=['evidence-685c493de602acb1']), PdfExtractionItem(label='principal conclusion', entity_type='conclusion', normalized_id=None, source_mentions=['Absolute quantification of proteins', 'molar ratios', 'molecular organization of the eye', 'mostly absolute quantification'], evidence_record_ids=['evidence-1a57b7477e69561f']), PdfExtractionItem(label='crb mutant protein-abundance finding', entity_type='result', normalized_id=None, source_mentions=['crb11A22', 'crb8F105', 'phototransduction proteins unchanged', 'Eys reduced in crb11A22'], evidence_record_ids=['evidence-a59255d797d89065'])] raw_mentions=[PdfMentionCandidate(mention='quantitative relationship between proteins of the PT machinery and Crumbs protein complex in wild-type and crb mutant fly eyes', entity_type='main biological question', evidence_record_ids=['evidence-90a17c9c05784b35']), PdfMentionCandidate(mention='Drosophila melanogaster eyes / wild-type flies / crumbs (crb) mutant eyes', entity_type='organism/model system', evidence_record_ids=['evidence-90a17c9c05784b35', 'evidence-685c493de602acb1']), PdfMentionCandidate(mention='MS Western with GeLC-MS/MS and isotopically labelled QconCAT-like CP standards', entity_type='experimental approach', evidence_record_ids=['evidence-685c493de602acb1']), PdfMentionCandidate(mention='absolute quantification revealed how molar ratios relate to molecular organization of the eye', entity_type='principal conclusion', evidence_record_ids=['evidence-1a57b7477e69561f']), PdfMentionCandidate(mention='rhabdomere shape changes in crb mutant alleles did not correlate with abundance of most PT proteins; Eys was reduced in crb11A22', entity_type='result', evidence_record_ids=['evidence-a59255d797d89065'])] evidence_records=[PdfEvidenceRecord(evidence_record_id='evidence-90a17c9c05784b35', entity='main biological question and model system', verified_quote='Rationale and Design of the Study\\nOur aim was to establish the quantitative relationship between proteins of the PT machinery and of the apical membraneorganizing Crumbs protein complex in different biological contexts.\\n\\nWe first quantified the molar abundances of PT proteins in a normally developed and fully functional wild-type fly eye and computed their basal molar ratios.\\n\\nNext, we used a series of crb mutants exhibiting different severity of impairment in rhabdomere morphology and compared molar abundances and ratios of PT proteins with the wild type.', page=1, section='Results and Discussion', chunk_id='95b61c29-576d-7386-cc81-869bc16e79ea', chunk_ids=['95b61c29-576d-7386-cc81-869bc16e79ea'], document_id='482538e8-13db-43e9-ad05-c159b68abb83', source_span_ids=['95b61c29-576d-7386-cc81-869bc16e79ea:s0003:c0205-c0424:7579faae', '95b61c29-576d-7386-cc81-869bc16e79ea:s0004:c0425-c0582:312f93cb', '95b61c29-576d-7386-cc81-869bc16e79ea:s0005:c0583-c0765:6dcc7f31'], source_fragments=[PdfEvidenceSourceFragment(span_id='95b61c29-576d-7386-cc81-869bc16e79ea:s0003:c0205-c0424:7579faae', chunk_id='95b61c29-576d-7386-cc81-869bc16e79ea', document_id='482538e8-13db-43e9-ad05-c159b68abb83', text='Rationale and Design of the Study\\nOur aim was to establish the quantitative relationship between proteins of the PT machinery and of the apical membraneorganizing Crumbs protein complex in different biological contexts.', char_start=205, char_end=424, text_hash='7579faae', page=1, section='Results and Discussion', subsection='Rationale and Design of the Study', figure_reference=None, span_index=3, span_type='sentence', spanizer_version='pdf_sentence_v1', anchor=None, bbox=None, bounding_boxes=None), PdfEvidenceSourceFragment(span_id='95b61c29-576d-7386-cc81-869bc16e79ea:s0004:c0425-c0582:312f93cb', chunk_id='95b61c29-576d-7386-cc81-869bc16e79ea', document_id='482538e8-13db-43e9-ad05-c159b68abb83', text='We first quantified the molar abundances of PT proteins in a normally developed and fully functional wild-type fly eye and computed their basal molar ratios.', char_start=425, char_end=582, text_hash='312f93cb', page=1, section='Results and Discussion', subsection='Rationale and Design of the Study', figure_reference=None, span_index=4, span_type='sentence', spanizer_version='pdf_sentence_v1', anchor=None, bbox=None, bounding_boxes=None), PdfEvidenceSourceFragment(span_id='95b61c29-576d-7386-cc81-869bc16e79ea:s0005:c0583-c0765:6dcc7f31', chunk_id='95b61c29-576d-7386-cc81-869bc16e79ea', document_id='482538e8-13db-43e9-ad05-c159b68abb83', text='Next, we used a series of crb mutants exhibiting different severity of impairment in rhabdomere morphology and compared molar abundances and ratios of PT proteins with the wild type.', char_start=583, char_end=765, text_hash='6dcc7f31', page=1, section='Results and Discussion', subsection='Rationale and Design of the Study', figure_reference=None, span_index=5, span_type='sentence', spanizer_version='pdf_sentence_v1', anchor=None, bbox=None, bounding_boxes=None)], subsection='Rationale and Design of the Study', figure_reference=None), PdfEvidenceRecord(evidence_record_id='evidence-685c493de602acb1', entity='key experimental approach', verified_quote='MS Western workflow is employed to determine molar abundances of proteins potentially critical for morphogenesis and phototransduction (PT) in eyes of Drosophila melanogaster using a single chimeric 264 kDa protein standard that covers, in total, 197 peptides from 43 proteins.\\n\\nFor the absolute quantification of proteins we employed the method of MS Western [9] that relies on GeLC-MS/MS and isotopically labelled QconCAT-like CP standards.\\n\\nFor this study, we designed a 264 kDa CP that, in total, encompassed 43 unique proteins; 12 of those were known key players in PT (e.g., Opsin-Rh1 / NinaE and G\u03b1q) and photoreceptor morphogenesis such as Crumbs (Crb), Chaoptin (Chp), Eyes Shut (Eys), and Prominin (Prom).', page=1, section='Abstract', chunk_id='f660824d-be9e-cd89-eace-5db25315a1d7', chunk_ids=['f660824d-be9e-cd89-eace-5db25315a1d7', '2ab1fbf2-880e-0659-d4db-7c52ce966a26'], document_id='482538e8-13db-43e9-ad05-c159b68abb83', source_span_ids=['f660824d-be9e-cd89-eace-5db25315a1d7:s0001:c0324-c0601:b2a0af5c', '2ab1fbf2-880e-0659-d4db-7c52ce966a26:s0002:c0200-c0363:753dd6e0', '2ab1fbf2-880e-0659-d4db-7c52ce966a26:s0003:c0364-c0635:5aec21d9'], source_fragments=[PdfEvidenceSourceFragment(span_id='f660824d-be9e-cd89-eace-5db25315a1d7:s0001:c0324-c0601:b2a0af5c', chunk_id='f660824d-be9e-cd89-eace-5db25315a1d7', document_id='482538e8-13db-43e9-ad05-c159b68abb83', text='MS Western workflow is employed to determine molar abundances of proteins potentially critical for morphogenesis and phototransduction (PT) in eyes of Drosophila melanogaster using a single chimeric 264 kDa protein standard that covers, in total, 197 peptides from 43 proteins.', char_start=324, char_end=601, text_hash='b2a0af5c', page=1, section='Abstract', subsection=None, figure_reference=None, span_index=1, span_type='sentence', spanizer_version='pdf_sentence_v1', anchor=None, bbox=None, bounding_boxes=None), PdfEvidenceSourceFragment(span_id='2ab1fbf2-880e-0659-d4db-7c52ce966a26:s0002:c0200-c0363:753dd6e0', chunk_id='2ab1fbf2-880e-0659-d4db-7c52ce966a26', document_id='482538e8-13db-43e9-ad05-c159b68abb83', text='For the absolute quantification of proteins we employed the method of MS Western [9] that relies on GeLC-MS/MS and isotopically labelled QconCAT-like CP standards.', char_start=200, char_end=363, text_hash='753dd6e0', page=1, section='Results and Discussion', subsection='Rationale and Design of the Study', figure_reference=None, span_index=2, span_type='sentence', spanizer_version='pdf_sentence_v1', anchor=None, bbox=None, bounding_boxes=None), PdfEvidenceSourceFragment(span_id='2ab1fbf2-880e-0659-d4db-7c52ce966a26:s0003:c0364-c0635:5aec21d9', chunk_id='2ab1fbf2-880e-0659-d4db-7c52ce966a26', document_id='482538e8-13db-43e9-ad05-c159b68abb83', text='For this study, we designed a 264 kDa CP that, in total, encompassed 43 unique proteins; 12 of those were known key players in PT (e.g., Opsin-Rh1 / NinaE and G\u03b1q) and photoreceptor morphogenesis such as Crumbs (Crb), Chaoptin (Chp), Eyes Shut (Eys), and Prominin (Prom).', char_start=364, char_end=635, text_hash='5aec21d9', page=1, section='Results and Discussion', subsection='Rationale and Design of the Study', figure_reference=None, span_index=3, span_type='sentence', spanizer_version='pdf_sentence_v1', anchor=None, bbox=None, bounding_boxes=None)], subsection=None, figure_reference=None), PdfEvidenceRecord(evidence_record_id='evidence-1a57b7477e69561f', entity='principal conclusion', verified_quote='Conclusions and Perspectives\\nAbsolute quantification of proteins in the two networks important for eye morphogenesis revealed how molar ratios are related to the molecular organization of the eye.\\n\\nOur study, which included wild-type flies and few mutant alleles, provided consistent values for several proteins at one-go using the MS Western workflow.\\n\\nBy showing good concordance with classical biochemistry our work advocates for changing the field paradigm from mostly relative to mostly absolute quantification.', page=1, section='Conclusions and Perspectives', chunk_id='6d40b079-6476-2016-8dad-39ffabd62874', chunk_ids=['6d40b079-6476-2016-8dad-39ffabd62874'], document_id='482538e8-13db-43e9-ad05-c159b68abb83', source_span_ids=['6d40b079-6476-2016-8dad-39ffabd62874:s0003:c0203-c0399:0e2a674f', '6d40b079-6476-2016-8dad-39ffabd62874:s0004:c0400-c0554:78a09a94', '6d40b079-6476-2016-8dad-39ffabd62874:s0006:c0706-c0868:f88d7c72'], source_fragments=[PdfEvidenceSourceFragment(span_id='6d40b079-6476-2016-8dad-39ffabd62874:s0003:c0203-c0399:0e2a674f', chunk_id='6d40b079-6476-2016-8dad-39ffabd62874', document_id='482538e8-13db-43e9-ad05-c159b68abb83', text='Conclusions and Perspectives\\nAbsolute quantification of proteins in the two networks important for eye morphogenesis revealed how molar ratios are related to the molecular organization of the eye.', char_start=203, char_end=399, text_hash='0e2a674f', page=1, section='Conclusions and Perspectives', subsection=None, figure_reference=None, span_index=3, span_type='sentence', spanizer_version='pdf_sentence_v1', anchor=None, bbox=None, bounding_boxes=None), PdfEvidenceSourceFragment(span_id='6d40b079-6476-2016-8dad-39ffabd62874:s0004:c0400-c0554:78a09a94', chunk_id='6d40b079-6476-2016-8dad-39ffabd62874', document_id='482538e8-13db-43e9-ad05-c159b68abb83', text='Our study, which included wild-type flies and few mutant alleles, provided consistent values for several proteins at one-go using the MS Western workflow.', char_start=400, char_end=554, text_hash='78a09a94', page=1, section='Conclusions and Perspectives', subsection=None, figure_reference=None, span_index=4, span_type='sentence', spanizer_version='pdf_sentence_v1', anchor=None, bbox=None, bounding_boxes=None), PdfEvidenceSourceFragment(span_id='6d40b079-6476-2016-8dad-39ffabd62874:s0006:c0706-c0868:f88d7c72', chunk_id='6d40b079-6476-2016-8dad-39ffabd62874', document_id='482538e8-13db-43e9-ad05-c159b68abb83', text='By showing good concordance with classical biochemistry our work advocates for changing the field paradigm from mostly relative to mostly absolute quantification.', char_start=706, char_end=868, text_hash='f88d7c72', page=1, section='Conclusions and Perspectives', subsection=None, figure_reference=None, span_index=6, span_type='sentence', spanizer_version='pdf_sentence_v1', anchor=None, bbox=None, bounding_boxes=None)], subsection=None, figure_reference=None), PdfEvidenceRecord(evidence_record_id='evidence-a59255d797d89065', entity='crb mutant protein-abundance finding', verified_quote='Intriguingly, we found that despite the gross abnormalities in rhabdomeres in crb11A22 and crb8F105, overall levels of most of the phototransduction proteins, that is, Opsin 1, Trp, NorpA, Arr1, and Arr2, were unchanged, whereas G\u03b1q was increased in crb8F105 only (Figure 5F).\\n\\nThus, rhabdomere shape changes in crb mutant alleles did not correlate with the abundance of PT proteins.\\n\\nIn contrast, Eys is significantly reduced in crb11A22 eyes (Figure 5G).', page=1, section='Results and Discussion', chunk_id='c29d3ce8-77f3-dd0e-1d7f-99fa60a30ed3', chunk_ids=['c29d3ce8-77f3-dd0e-1d7f-99fa60a30ed3'], document_id='482538e8-13db-43e9-ad05-c159b68abb83', source_span_ids=['c29d3ce8-77f3-dd0e-1d7f-99fa60a30ed3:s0004:c0480-c0756:38c8927f', 'c29d3ce8-77f3-dd0e-1d7f-99fa60a30ed3:s0005:c0757-c0862:d763a006', 'c29d3ce8-77f3-dd0e-1d7f-99fa60a30ed3:s0009:c1300-c1371:124b3af4'], source_fragments=[PdfEvidenceSourceFragment(span_id='c29d3ce8-77f3-dd0e-1d7f-99fa60a30ed3:s0004:c0480-c0756:38c8927f', chunk_id='c29d3ce8-77f3-dd0e-1d7f-99fa60a30ed3', document_id='482538e8-13db-43e9-ad05-c159b68abb83', text='Intriguingly, we found that despite the gross abnormalities in rhabdomeres in crb11A22 and crb8F105, overall levels of most of the phototransduction proteins, that is, Opsin 1, Trp, NorpA, Arr1, and Arr2, were unchanged, whereas G\u03b1q was increased in crb8F105 only (Figure 5F).', char_start=480, char_end=756, text_hash='38c8927f', page=1, section='Results and Discussion', subsection='Changes in Molecular Organization Following Abnormal PRC Development in crumbs Mutants', figure_reference=None, span_index=4, span_type='sentence', spanizer_version='pdf_sentence_v1', anchor=None, bbox=None, bounding_boxes=None), PdfEvidenceSourceFragment(span_id='c29d3ce8-77f3-dd0e-1d7f-99fa60a30ed3:s0005:c0757-c0862:d763a006', chunk_id='c29d3ce8-77f3-dd0e-1d7f-99fa60a30ed3', document_id='482538e8-13db-43e9-ad05-c159b68abb83', text='Thus, rhabdomere shape changes in crb mutant alleles did not correlate with the abundance of PT proteins.', char_start=757, char_end=862, text_hash='d763a006', page=1, section='Results and Discussion', subsection='Changes in Molecular Organization Following Abnormal PRC Development in crumbs Mutants', figure_reference=None, span_index=5, span_type='sentence', spanizer_version='pdf_sentence_v1', anchor=None, bbox=None, bounding_boxes=None), PdfEvidenceSourceFragment(span_id='c29d3ce8-77f3-dd0